description:
At AJBoggs, people are our greatest asset!



Accelerate your career today by supporting public sector organizations as an OnBase Engineer.



This role may be right for you if you:* Are detailed oriented and enjoy coordinating multiple teams in an Agile environment.
* Multitask in a fast-paced environment while remaining focused.
* Have excellent interpersonal, written, and oral communication skills.

 **ESSENTIAL RESPONSIBILITIES AND DUTIES**



Your essential duties and responsibilities include, but are not limited to, the following:

* Collaborate with others to determine functional and non-functional product requirements;
* Develop high-level product specifications with attention to integration and overall feasibility;
* Participate or lead specialized projects with other functional groups as required;
* Assist in the overall development and maintenance of the MiFILE system;
* Demonstrate high technical competency in all areas of OnBase API offerings;
* Understand MiFILE, the API services, case management systems, and how they all interact;
* Understand business requirements and how the APIs can be used to meet those requirements;
* Collaborate with API architects and developers in creating and maintaining API documentation;
* Meet with internal and external clients to gather requirements for building API resources that meet the needs of our stakeholders;
* Work with various teams to refine API governance, analytics and monitoring solutions;
* Understand REST fundamentals and API design best practices;
* Follow industry best practices and software development life cycle methodologies;
* Participate in Agile ceremonies and practices such as pairing, continuous integration, retrospectives, and backlog refinement;
* Maintain and expand professional and technical knowledge through research, training, and empirical testing; and
* Any other duties assigned.







### **Requirements**

* Bachelor’s degree in computer science, information technology, or a related field; or, college level coursework or equivalent combination of education and experience in analyzing, designing, testing, and documenting production systems;
* 2+ years of managing and developing enterprise solutions in Hyland’s OnBase platform;
* 2+ years of software development and coding in various languages (C#, Java, .NET, etc.);
* 1+ years of interface development involving OnBase;
* Familiar with REST fundamentals and API design best practices;

* API design tools, such as SwaggerHub or Stoplight;
* API Management platforms, such as Microsoft Azure API Management or Google Apigee;
* Agile development practices such as continuous integration/continuous delivery, backlog refinement, and retrospectives;
* Hyland Developer Specialist (previously OCAPI) – preferred;
* OnBase Administrator (previously OCSA or OCASA) – preferred;
* OnBase WorkView Administrator (previously OCWV) – preferred;
* OnBase Workflow Administrator (previously OCWA) – preferred;
* Communicate effectively, both verbally and in writing;
* Facilitate working meetings, elicit and solicit information, and absorb the information being communicated; facilitate a shared understanding of the problem, possible solutions, and scope of the project in its entirety; facilitate solutions to technical challenges among multiple teams when they involve negotiation between multiple business and technical stakeholders;
* Apply critical thinking skills to determine the appropriateness of requests, with periodic reviews of business procedures to clarify or change a business process. Use the knowledge gained in the daily operational procedures as input to business process and procedure documentation;
* Prioritize across multiple tasks in a fast-paced environment to meet deadlines; and
* Family members consider you to have a good sense of humor.

### **Benefits**


The salary for this position depends upon your qualifications, experience, skill levels, technical competencies, and other criteria. Straight-time overtime is occasionally available.  

Here are some of our other benefits:

* Group Medical, Dental, Life, HSA/FSA, and Vision Insurance;
* SIMPLE IRA Accounts with an immediate vesting of 3% company match;
* Paid company holidays and personal days;
* Partial Internet and mobile phone expense reimbursement;
* Collaborative and innovative work environment;
* Professional development opportunities; and
* Hybrid/remote work arrangement (subject to change).
